      "avalancheActivity": {
        "comment": "Early morning: The surface of the snowpack will freeze to form a strong crust. <br/> From late morning the natural activity of avalanches will increase. <br/> In particular in starting zones where no previous releases have taken place and on very steep slopes more medium-sized and, in isolated cases, large natural wet avalanches are possible. <br/> The conditions are generally favourable for ski touring. Backcountry tours and ascents to alpine cabins should be concluded timely. <br/> <br/> Since Sunday mostly small wind slabs formed especially above approximately 3000 m.",
        "highlights": "The danger of moist and wet avalanches will increase quickly during the day."
